igh temperature photons, cold electrons are pumped from the left to the right lead transversing through the junction of the lower energy levels of the quantum dots, while an equal amount of hot electrons are pumped the other way at the junction of the higher energy levels. The result is a net replacement of hot electrons by cold electrons in the right lead, implying its refrigeration. A qualitative explanation goes as follows. Consider first the distributions of electrons in the lead.},
  Doi                      = {10.1103/PhysRevLett.108.120603},
  File                     = {Articles\Cleuren-PRL108-120603-2012.pdf}
}

