  Abstract                 = {In a recent work [Phys. Rev. A 84, 033804 (2011)] we considered elastic scattering of a twisted particle from a plane wave and studied how the orbital helicity of the twisted particle changes after scattering.We showed that for realistic beams the relative change can be small, |m  - m|/m  1, thus resolving a controversy which existed in the literature. In this Addendum, using a more accurate analysis, we argue that in the kinematics of Compton backscattering a stronger statement is true: in fact m  â m, and the difference |m  - m| even by a single unit is already suppressed.},
